I made a new friend today. 😘🐬

Thank you, @sixflagsdiscoverykingdom, for having us!!

March is Women’s History Month. Today we wanted to spotlight @wrestlingleva she is a mental health advocate, an @aew superstar and can be seen empowering and making a huge difference for a female-forward movement in the lives of many women over at @aew_heels we sincerely thank Leva for taking the time out of her day to show our page love and become one of our favorite followers and partners in making mental health conversations matter. Leva is a true advocate for mental health and takes great pride in celebrating and inspiring not just women but every human being she comes into contact with. The world is truly stronger and kinder today because of her. Thank you Leva for being our champion in and out of the ring. 

This is the first spotlight of many to come. Soon we will see the amazing women behind the scenes of @youaremore988 who are representing states all across the US. and Canada. We wouldn’t be who we are without these amazing ambassadors of mental health. Happy March! Happy Women’s History Month!

Story time: years ago I was doing the pants of blue thing. I was nervous & absolutely anxious, since I was the odd one out. I wasn’t signed, but I was being used a lot. I felt like a thorn in most people’s sides because this was kind of unheard at the time. 
But one day in catering, Bray randomly struck up a conversation with me. Honestly about nothing, small talk and whatnot, but he oddly put me at ease. He didn’t have to do that, but he did. He probably didn’t even think anything of it, but it meant a lot to me. 

So today I honor Bray Wyatt one of the only ways I know how: to wrestle as him. Thank you, Bray, for the entertainment, inspiration and your kindness

2023 turned out way different than I expected & I couldn’t be happier for it! 
It was a year of self discovery & growth. Growth as a performer, businesswoman & human being.
